Eight people escaped death narrowly after a lorry ploughed through roadside traders at Awasi market in Kisumu county. Nyando OCPD Fannuel Nasio said the victims - four men and four women - were selling their wares at that time. They were seriously injured in the Saturday incident and are being treated at Ahero hospital where they rushed were by well-wishers. Nasio said the accident could have been caused by faulty brakes but investigations are ongoing to ascertain the real cause. The police boss said the driver of the lorry, which was headed to Kisumu, sped off probably for fear that members of the public would have set the vehicle ablaze. "So far, we have impounded the lorry and arrested the driver who is currently in our custody," Nasio said. Click here for the latest political news   